videos.description: Kelly Bryant connects with Deon Cain for a 28-yard touchdown on the Tigers' first drive of the game.
videos.headline: Bryant to Cain for Clemson's first TD

videos.description: Travis Etienne breaks a tackle and runs for 20 yards to keep Clemson's drive alive.
videos.headline: Etienne turns a loss into a first down

videos.description: Adam Choice bounces off two defenders for a four-yard rushing touchdown for Clemson.
videos.headline: Choice barrels through for a TD

videos.description: Kendall Hinton finds Greg Dortch over the middle who works across the field for a 44-yard reception for Wake Forest.
videos.headline: Dortch gets free for huge Wake Forest gain

videos.description: Clemson Head Coach Dabo Swinney says his offense is performing well despite Wake Forest's defensive pressure in the first half.
videos.headline: Swinney: 'Playing well despite Wake Forest defense'

videos.description: Clemson QB Kelly Bryant throws an interception to Amari Henderson early in the third quarter.
videos.headline: Bryant picked off by Wake Forest

videos.description: Wake Forest QB Kendall Hinton connects with Chuck Wade for a 38-yard reception over the middle after the Clemson turnover.
videos.headline: Hinton finds Wade for 38 yards

videos.description: Travis Etienne takes it in from one yard out for a Clemson touchdown.
videos.headline: Etienne takes in a short TD

videos.description: Kelly Bryant injures his ankle on an eight-yard run and leaves the game after a Clemson touchdown.
videos.headline: Bryant leaves game with ankle injury

videos.description: Kelly Bryant appears to injure his ankle on an eight-yard run in the red zone as he's tackled. He would leave the game after a Clemson score.
videos.headline: Bryant shaken up on run

videos.description: True freshman Hunter Johnson comes into the game for Kelly Bryant and throws a 13-yard touchdown to Cannon Smith.
videos.headline: Johnson  throws first career TD

videos.description: Kendall Hinton throws a 16-yard touchdown to Scotty Washington for the Deacons first touchdown of the game.
videos.headline: Hinton get Wake Forest on the board

videos.description: Kendall Hinton escapes pressure and takes it 37 yards into the red zone for Wake Forest.
videos.headline: Hinton gets huge gain on the ground

videos.description: Kendall Hinton finds Cam Serigne in the corner of the end zone for an 11-yard touchdown.
videos.headline: Serigne gets open for Wake Forest TD

videos.description: Beth Mowins and Anthony Becht break down Kelly Bryant's performance in win against Wake Forest before leaving the game with an ankle injury.
videos.headline: Bryant ultra-efficient before injury
